    <description>En Pointe Toujours !: Vent du Nord sur Hatten (Always ahead !: North wind on Hatten) is a campaign for En Pointe Toujours ! tactical wargame during the Nordwind Operation in Alsace (eastern France), January 1945.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game includes 75 counters to mount and an A4-size map (map S). Rules are not included but available on Vae Victis website along with a bonus scenario.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The campaign covers 4 different scenarios :&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     &amp;quot;Surprise &amp;agrave; l'Aube&amp;quot; (Surprise at dawn). Hatten 1945 (15 turns): Elements of the US 1st Battalion/242nd Infantry Regiment/42nd Infantry Division against Elements of the 25th Panzer Grenadier Division. This scenario uses 4 maps (G, H, I, J) available from Vae Victis 51 issue.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     &amp;quot;Mourir pour Hatten&amp;quot; (Die for Hatten). Hatten 1945 (10 turns): Elements of the US 2nd Battalion/242nd Infantry Regiment/42nd Infantry Division and 48th Tank Battalion/14th Armored Division against Elements of the 25th Panzer Grenadier Division. This scenario uses 6 maps (A, C, G, H, I, J) available from Vae Victis 31 and 51.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     &amp;quot;Sherman Ball Trap&amp;quot;. Herrlisheim 1945 (5 turns): C squadron/43rd Tank Battalion against elements of Volksgrenadier Division 553. This scenario uses 4 maps (K, L, N , H) available from Vae Victis HS6 and 51.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     &amp;quot;Assaut sur Wingen&amp;quot; (Assault on Wingen). Wingen 1945 (5 turns): Elements of 1st Battalion/179th Infantry Regiment against Elements of 12th regiment/6th SS Nord Division. This scenario uses 1 map (map S included).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
